><section class="ReviewText"><section class="ReviewText__content"><div class="TruncatedText"><div class="TruncatedText__text TruncatedText__text--5" data-testid="contentContainer"><div><span class="Formatted"><b>"The fighting doesn't start until Koom Valley Day. That's tomorrow."<br /><br />"Damn, I lost track. Will it affect us down here?"<br /><br />Bashfullsson coughed politely. "I don't think so, Commander. This area is too dangerous to fight in."<br /><br />"Well, yes, I can see it would be terrible if anyone got hurt," said Vimes, climbing over a long heap of rotting timber. "That would spoil the day for everyone."</b><br /><br />While the main mystery of this one - a dwarf is <i>apparently</i> murdered by a troll - didn't interest me much, there are plenty of other shenanigans to make this Discworld adventure a fun read. I really enjoyed the heck out of Angua and Cheery's <i>Girl's Night Out</i> with a vampire and a stripper, and then there was the memorable road trip to Koom Valley. <br /><br />Even in Discworld, historical reenactments blow.</span></div></div></div></section></section><section class="ReviewCard__tags"><ul class="CollapsableList"><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/5293536?shelf=fantasy" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">fantasy</span></a> <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/5293536?shelf=humorous-fiction" class="Button Button--tag-inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelItem">humorous-fiction</span></a></ul></section><footer class="SocialFooter"><div data-testid="stats" class="SocialFooter__statsContainer"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small Button--subdued"><span class="Button__labelItem">18 likes</span></button></div></div><div data-testid="actions"><div class="SocialFooter__action"><div class="Button__container"><button type="button" class="Button Button--inline Button--small"><span class="Button__labelI